# Insights & Analytics Engine

The insights engine is the core differentiator. Most tools give a percentage score. We give a breakdown that tells users _why_ they match and _what to do about it_. Each insight is a standalone module — built, shipped, and tested independently.

## Architecture

### Data Flow

```
ParsedResume + ParsedJob
       ↓
  Matching Engine (AI-powered comparison)
       ↓
  Overall Score + Per-Insight Results
       ↓
  Tabbed Results UI
```

### Module Pattern

Every insight follows the same structure:

```
src/services/insights/
  types.ts                    # Shared InsightResult interface
  insight-registry.ts         # Maps insight IDs to implementations
  score/
    overall-score.ts          # #1 — compute + format
    overall-score.prompt.ts   # Prompt template
    overall-score.schema.ts   # Zod output schema
  skills-breakdown/
    ...
```

Each insight module exports:
- **`compute(resume, job, options)`** — runs the AI call or algorithm, returns structured result
- **`schema`** — Zod schema validating the AI output
- **`prompt`** — TypeScript function building the prompt from parsed inputs

### Display Component Requirements

Every insight display component **must** include:
- **Title icon** — a Lucide React icon placed before the title in the `<h3>` heading, sized `h-5 w-5` with an appropriate color. Icon choice should reflect the insight's purpose:
  - Overall Match Score → `Target` (primary)
  - Skills Match Breakdown → `Puzzle` (blue-500)
  - Top 3 Action Items → `Lightbulb` (yellow-500)
  - Top Strengths → `Trophy` (amber-500)
- Icons are **required** for all current and future insights — no insight card ships without one

### Result Envelope

```typescript
interface InsightResult<T> {
  id: string;                    // e.g. "overall-score"
  name: string;                  // e.g. "Overall Match Score"
  tier: 1 | 2 | 3;
  tab: "shared" | "jobseeker" | "hiring-manager";
  status: "success" | "partial" | "error";
  data: T;                       // Insight-specific typed payload
  computedAt: string;            // ISO timestamp
  modelUsed: string;             // e.g. "gpt-4o-mini"
  tokensUsed: number;
}
```

### Tier Gating

| Tier | Visibility | Access |
|------|-----------|--------|
| 1 | Always shown in full | Guest + Free + Lifetime |
| 2 | Teaser shown (blurred/truncated), full behind gate | Free (limited) + Lifetime (full) |
| 3 | Locked with preview description | Lifetime only |

Gating is applied at the UI layer, not the API — all insights are computed for all users to enable instant unlock on upgrade. Cached results remain valid after tier change.

### Caching

- Cache key: `hash(resume_text + job_text + insight_id + model)`
- Storage: `ai_cache` table in Supabase
- TTL: indefinite (same inputs always produce same insight)
- Identical resume+job pairs skip AI calls entirely

## Results UI

### Tabbed Layout

```
┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Overall Match Score: 78%  [ring gauge]   │
├───────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  [ For Jobseekers ]  [ For Hiring Mgrs ] │
│  ─────────────────────────────────────    │
│  (insight cards render below in tab)      │
└───────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Shared insights** appear in both tabs, framed per audience
- **Exclusive insights** appear only in their designated tab
- Each insight renders as a card with title, status badge, and expandable content

