### #3 — Top 3 Action Items

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Tab** | Jobseeker only |
| **Tier** | 1 (always available) |
| **Phase** | MVP |

**Why it matters**
Turns analysis into action. Jobseekers don't just want to know what's wrong — they want to know what to do _first_. This is the "so what?" that competitors miss. Drives repeat usage and upgrades.

**Implementation**
- AI analyzes the gap between resume and job requirements
- Generates 3 prioritized, specific recommendations ranked by impact on match score
- Each action item references a specific resume section and suggests concrete wording

**Output schema**
```typescript
z.object({
  actions: z.array(z.object({
    priority: z.number().min(1).max(3),
    title: z.string(),           // e.g., "Add Kubernetes to your skills"
    description: z.string(),     // Why this matters + how to do it
    section: z.string(),         // Which resume section to edit
    impact: z.enum(["high", "medium"]),
  })).length(3),
})
```

**How to interpret**
- Ordered by impact — action #1 moves the score the most
- Each action targets a specific resume section for easy editing
- "High impact" = directly addresses a required skill/qualification

